JOHANNESBURG - Independent Police Investigative Directorate, boss Robert McBride is expected back in the Pretoria Magistrate’s Court, on assault charges.
	
	In August a teen claimed McBride beat and strangled her. READ: McBride denies assault allegations The teen has since obtained a protection order. The IPID head however denies the allegation, saying he merely scolded her. He's out on R10,000 bail. eNCA